      "source": [
        "## 3. ***Data Wrangling***"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "F_QOMs-BiBow"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Data Wrangling Code"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "HnkEcpuwiBow"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# ── Step 1: Drop rows with null track_name or artists ──\n",
        "df.dropna(subset=['track_name', 'artists'], inplace=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ── Step 2: Remove duplicated track_id entries (keep first) ──\n",
        "df.drop_duplicates(subset='track_id', keep='first', inplace=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ── Step 3: Convert duration from ms to minutes for readability ──\n",
        "df['duration_min'] = df['duration_ms'] / 60000\n",
        "\n",
        "# ── Step 4: Convert explicit from bool to int for correlation analysis ──\n",
        "df['explicit_int'] = df['explicit'].astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ── Step 5: Filter out extreme outliers in duration (< 0.5 min or > 15 min) ──\n",
        "df = df[(df['duration_min'] >= 0.5) & (df['duration_min'] <= 15)]\n",
        "\n",
        "# ── Step 6: Bin popularity into categories for categorical analysis ──\n",
        "df['popularity_tier'] = pd.cut(\n",
        "    df['popularity'],\n",
        "    bins=[0, 20, 40, 60, 80, 100],\n",
        "    labels=['Very Low', 'Low', 'Medium', 'High', 'Very High'],\n",
        "    include_lowest=True\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print('Data wrangling complete!')\n",
        "print(f'Final dataset shape: {df.shape}')"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "sMo9pwJQiBow"
      },
      "source": [
        "### What all manipulations have you done and insights you found?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mke0jhPiiBox"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Manipulations performed:**\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Dropped null rows** for `track_name` and `artists` — these are essential identifiers and rows without them are not usable.\n",
        "2. **Removed duplicate `track_id` entries** — some tracks appear across multiple genre labels. Keeping only the first occurrence ensures each track is counted once.\n",
        "3. **Created `duration_min`** — converting milliseconds to minutes makes the column human-readable and easier to interpret in visualisations.\n",
        "4. **Created `explicit_int`** — boolean-to-integer conversion enables correlation analysis with numerical audio features.\n",
        "5. **Filtered extreme duration outliers** — tracks under 30 seconds (intros, skits) and over 15 minutes (live sets, extended mixes) were removed to focus on standard commercial tracks.\n",
        "6. **Created `popularity_tier`** — binning popularity into 5 categories enables categorical analysis and clearer visualisations comparing audio features across popularity segments.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Insights from wrangling:** The dataset is remarkably clean. The main data quality issue was duplicate tracks appearing under multiple genre labels. After deduplication, the dataset represents a diverse cross-section of Spotify's catalogue."
      ]
    },
